  "prompt": "Why was MM kalburgi killed?",
  "response": "M.M. Kalburgi, an Indian rationalist and scholar, was killed on August 30, 2015, in Karnataka, India. He was known for his critical views on superstition, blind faith, and religious dogmas. Kalburgi's murder is believed to be linked to his outspoken criticism of certain religious beliefs and practices, particularly in Hinduism, as well as his advocacy for reason and scientific inquiry.\n\nHis assassination was seen as part of a broader trend of attacks against scholars and activists who challenge religious orthodoxy and promote rationalism in India. His death prompted widespread condemnation and discussions about freedom of expression, secularism, and the safety of intellectuals and dissenters in the country. Police investigations and public discourse suggested that his murder was motivated by his views and writings, which had angered certain extremist groups or individuals.",
